


conda create -n mlflow_server python=3.11 -y

conda activate mlflow_server

pip install mlflow


mlflow_server env
    ↓
MLflow tracking server (local)
    ↓
SQLite DB (runs)
    ↓
Artifacts folder (models/files)
    ↓
ngrok tunnel (RunPod access)


cd ~/mlflow_server


mlflow server \
  --host 0.0.0.0 \
  --port 56288 \
  --backend-store-uri sqlite:///mlflow.db \
  --default-artifact-root ./artifacts \
  --serve-artifacts


✅ Step 1 — Create ngrok account


Go here:

👉 https://dashboard.ngrok.com/signup

Sign up (Google login is fastest).

✅ Step 2 — Get your authtoken

Go here:

👉 https://dashboard.ngrok.com/get-started/your-authtoken

You’ll see a command like:
ngrok config add-authtoken YOUR_TOKEN_HERE


  ngrok http 56288

  Always:

Start MLflow → note port
Start ngrok → same port
Keep both running